<h2>Your Account</h2>


<div class="form-group">
  <label>It looks like you’ve already started saving for your Car Purchase and Emergency Savings goal in a bank account. How would you like us to approach this goal?</label>
  <div class="help-block">We recommend having your savings in separate account than your day-to-day checking or banking account that you use to pay bills – that way you won’t be tempted!</div>

  <div class="radio">
    <label>
      {{radio-button value='dreamForward' checked=shortTermLocation}}
      I’d like to save for the remaining about of money I need for these goals in a Dream Forward bank account that automatically deducts from each paycheck.
    </label>
  </div>
  <div class="radio">
    <label>
      {{radio-button value='directDeposit' checked=shortTermLocation}}
      Help me set up direct deposit so Dream Forward can transfer the right amount of money from my paycheck to my existing outside account where I’m already saving.
    </label>
  </div>
  <div class="radio">
    <label>
      {{radio-button value='personal' checked=shortTermLocation}}
      Just keep it in my personal saving map, but don’t deduct from my paycheck for it. I’ll handle it.
    </label>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="form-group">
  <label>It looks like you’ve already started investing in a brokerage account for your College goal. How would you like us to approach this goal?</label>
  <div class="help-block">We recommend you have a separate brokerage account for your financial goals so you’re not tempted to try to be a stock trader and beat the market.</div>
  <div class="radio">
    <label>
      {{radio-button value='directDeposit' checked=longTermLocation}}
      I’d like use a Dream Forward brokerage account just for my financial goals, automatically deducing the right amount of money from each paycheck.
    </label>
  </div>
  <div class="radio">
    <label>
      {{radio-button value='personal' checked=longTermLocation}}
      Just keep it in my personal saving map, but don’t deduct from my paycheck. I’ll handle it.
    </label>
  </div>
</div>

{{#link-to 'dashboard'}}<div class="btn btn-success">Save</div>{{/link-to}}